{"ts": "2026-06-06T14:21:20.000Z", "event": "report", "msg": "Brand report assembly", "agent": "brand-report-l1", "tokens_in": 1904, "tokens_out": 1506, "elapsed_ms": 25394, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Brand Report agent. Merge all worker results below into a clean, well-structured Markdown report.\n\n## Worker Results\n### palette\nThe color palette has been generated and validated as requested. Here's the summary:\n\n✅ **palette.json** created with 8 colors:\n- Primary: `#3d87cc`\n- Secondary: `#b75088`\n- Accent (Research/Analytics): `#80cc20`\n- Neutrals: `#f4f7f9`, `#d5d7d8`, `#8a8b8c`, `#585859`, `#1e1e1e`\n\n✅ **palette-preview.html** created with visual swatches and contrast analysis.\n\n⚠️ **Contrast Notes**:\n- Text `#fafafa` on dark `#1e1e1e`: ✅ 15.97:1 (AAA compliant)\n- Text `#fafafa` on terminal `#69696b`: ✅ 5.25:1 (AA compliant)\n- Primary `#3d87cc` on `#1e1e1e`: 4.39:1 → ❌ Fails AA for normal text (needs adjustment)\n- Secondary `#b75088` on `#1e1e1e`: 3.59:1 → ❌ Fails AA for normal text (needs adjustment)\n- Accent `#80cc20` on `#1e1e1e`: ✅ 8.4:1 (AAA compliant)\n\n> 💡 **Recommendation**: Adjust primary and secondary colors to increase contrast (e.g., lighten or darken slightly) to meet WCAG AA for normal text. The current palette is suitable for UI elements and large text, but not for small body text on dark backgrounds.\n\nAll files saved in workspace:\n- `/palette.json`\n- `/palette-preview.html`\n\n### logo\nAll brand assets for Orcheeos have been successfully generated and organized:\n\n### ✅ Logo & Favicon\n- **`logo.svg`**: Full-color logo featuring a stylized geometric '0'/orrery motif with precision lines and subtle purple-blue glow (`#3d87cc` + `#80cc20` radial gradient). Includes the logotype \"Orcheeos\" in Inter font.\n- **`favicon.svg`**: Optimized 32x32 version for browser tabs, preserving the core geometric mark.\n\n### ✅ Icon Set\n- **12 SVG icons** generated in `icons/` directory:  \n  `home`, `search`, `settings`, `user`, `heart`, `star`, `mail`, `phone`, `lock`, `check`, `close`, `menu`  \n  - Style: Line (1.5px stroke), 24x24px canvas, color `#3d87cc`  \n  - All icons are scalable, consistent, and ready for UI integration.\n\n### ✅ Documentation\n- **`README.md`**: Comprehensive brand asset guide with file locations and usage notes.\n- **`palette.json`**: Validated color palette with contrast ratios (already generated).\n\n### ✅ Verification\n- All SVGs were visually verified using `read_image` (base64 inspection confirmed correct rendering).\n- File structure is clean and production-ready.\n\nAll assets are now available in the workspace for immediate use in web, app, or print applications.\n\n### typography\nTypography system for Orcheeos has been successfully defined and exported:\n\n✅ **`typography.json`** created with:\n- **Heading font**: Inter (sans-serif) — sizes: 3rem (48px), 2rem (32px), 1.5rem (24px), 1.25rem (20px)\n- **Body & code font**: JetBrains Mono (monospace) — body at 0.875rem (14px), code at 0.8125rem (13px)\n- **Letter-spacing**: Headings at -0.02em, logo lockup at 0.1em (tracked-out caps)\n- **Line heights**: Headings 1.2, body 1.6\n- **Weights**: 400, 500, 600, 700\n- **Google Fonts URL** included for easy integration\n\n✅ **`typography-preview.html`** created with live specimen showing:\n- All heading levels\n- Body text in Inter\n- Code blocks in JetBrains Mono\n- Logo lockup in tracked-out uppercase Inter\n- Dark code background for terminal aesthetic\n\nAll files saved in workspace:\n- `/typography.json`\n- `/typography-preview.html`\n\nThe system aligns with Orcheeos’ technical, precise brand personality — clean sans-serif for human readability, monospace for data/code authenticity, and elevated logo treatment for brand distinction.\n\n### images\nThe 6 concept icons have been successfully generated and packaged into `icons.zip` as requested. Each icon follows the angular, geometric, terminal-inspired aesthetic with glowing accents in the brand’s designated colors.\n\n✅ **Icons Generated**:\n- `agent_node.svg`\n- `orchestration_gear.svg`\n- `trace_path.svg`\n- `study_matrix.svg`\n- `langgraph_diamond.svg`\n- `code_file.svg`\n\n✅ **Format**: All icons were generated as high-resolution PNGs (vector-style illustrations), then bundled into a ZIP archive.\n\n✅ **Verification**:\n- All files confirmed present via `ls -la icons/`\n- ZIP archive created successfully with `zip -r icons.zip icons/`\n\n📁 **Output**: `icons.zip` is now available in the workspace root for download or integration.\n\nAll tasks completed.\n\n### guide\nERROR: Provider returned error\n\n### tester\nThe SVG files for the logo and favicon are valid. However, the color palette has significant WCAG contrast issues. The primary, secondary, and accent colors fail WCAG AA for normal text against most neutral background colors. The accent color also fails WCAG AA for large text against several neutral colors. The typography JSON is valid.\n\nI have generated a `test_report.json` file summarizing these findings. The next step should be to revise the color palette to ensure accessibility compliance.\n\n## Files Created (including brand_guide.html — the visual presentation)\n- palette-preview.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- palette.json: {\"primary\": \"#3d87cc\", \"secondary\": \"#b75088\", \"accent\": \"#80cc20\", \"neutral_100\": \"#f4f7f9\", \"neutr\n- README.md: # Orcheeos Brand Identity\n- favicon.svg: <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 32 32\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\">\n- logo.svg: <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 200\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\">\n- output.svg: <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 400 120\" width=\"400\" height=\"120\">\n- typography-preview.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- typography.json: {\n- icons/agent_node.svg: SVG image\n- icons/code_file.svg: SVG image\n- icons/langgraph_diamond.svg: SVG image\n- icons/orchestration_gear.svg: SVG image\n- icons/study_matrix.svg: SVG image\n- icons/trace_path.svg: SVG image\n- icons.zip: File (.zip)\n- requirements.txt: reportlab\n- usage_rules.md: # Orcheeos Brand Usage Guidelines\n- test_report.json: {\n- execute.sh: #!/bin/bash\n- install_and_export.sh: #!/bin/bash\n- install_deps.sh: #!/bin/bash\n- run_install.sh: #!/bin/bash\n- install_and_run.sh: #!/bin/bash\n\n## Tester Issues\n[\n  {\n    \"asset\": \"logo.svg\",\n    \"passed\": true,\n    \"issue\": null\n  },\n  {\n    \"asset\": \"favicon.svg\",\n    \"passed\": true,\n    \"issue\": null\n  },\n  {\n    \"asset\": \"palette.json\",\n    \"passed\": false,\n    \"issue\": \"WCAG contrast issues found. See summary for details.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"asset\": \"typography.json\",\n    \"passed\": true,\n    \"issue\": null\n  }\n]\n\n## Guidelines\n- Group results logically (palette, logo, typography, images, guide)\n- Include a summary table at the top with worker name, status, and a one-liner\n- Highlight any errors or tester issues prominently\n- Mention brand_guide.html as the visual reference\n- Reference file paths for created assets\n- Keep the report concise but complete\n\nOutput the full Markdown report.", "meta": {}}
